.TH simple_Shell "man page" "April - 2020"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Executes commands.
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "holberton.h"
int main(int argc, char *argv[], char **env);
.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is a program that takes some commands from the keyboard and gives them to the operating system to perform.
.SH OPTIONS
Commands that you can execute in the simple_shell (you can see the diferent options in the manual of each command, puts in the terminal > man 'nameofcommand').
.B Basic simple_shell Commands:
ls: Display the list of all the files and directories.
cat: Display the content of a file.
pwd: Show the current directory.
touch: Create file(s).
mkdir: Create a directory(ies).
cp: Copy files and directories.
mv: Move file and directories or change the name of them.
rm: Remove files or directories.
rmdir: Delete a directory if it is empty.
chown: Change the owner of file:
chmod: Modify the access/permission of a file.
grep: Search for the specified text in a file.
sort: Sort contents of files.
wc: Cont the number of characters, words in a file.
cut: Cut a specified part of a file.
.SH BUGS
None known.
